PROJECT TITLE

Multi-User Docker-Based Web Application Deployment with Persistent Storage Management

ABSTRACT

This project demonstrates Linux user administration and Docker container management in a multi-user environment. Multiple Linux users were created and assigned different Docker-related responsibilities. A custom Docker image was built using Dockerfile and deployed as a web application. Docker volumes were implemented to provide persistent storage and verify data availability even after container deletion.

OBJECTIVE

• Create Linux users and assign responsibilities.
• Install and configure Docker Engine.
• Create a custom Docker image.
• Deploy a web application using Docker containers.
• Create and manage Docker volumes.
• Verify persistent storage using Docker volumes.

TECHNOLOGIES USED

• Linux
• Docker
• Dockerfile
• HTML
• SSH
• Docker Volumes

