---

TASK-1 : DOCKER IMAGE MANAGEMENT

Assigned User : Sai

Commands:

nano index.html

Content: 

nano Dockerfile

Content:

FROM nginx

COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html

docker build -t suresh .

docker images

Description:

A custom web page and Dockerfile were created. Using the Docker build command, a custom image named "suresh" was generated for application deployment.

Output:

Custom Docker image created successfully.

Image Name : suresh

---

TASK-2 : CONTAINER CREATION

Assigned User : Venkatesh

Commands:

docker run -itd --name vks -p 8080:80 suresh  bash

docker ps

docker ps -a

Description:

A Docker container named vks was created using the custom image suresh and deployed successfully.

Output:

Container Name : vks

Status : Running

---

TASK-3 : CONTAINER MONITORING

Assigned User : Narayana

Commands:

docker ps

docker inspect vks

docker logs vks

docker stats

Description:

The running container was monitored using Docker commands. Container status and logs were verified successfully.

Output:

Container monitored successfully.

---

TASK-4 : CONTAINER OPERATIONS

Assigned User : Kasim

Commands:

docker stop vks

docker start vks

docker restart vks

Description:

Container lifecycle operations such as stop, start, and restart were performed successfully.

Output:

Container operations completed successfully.

---

TASK-5 : DOCKER VOLUME CREATION

Assigned User : Paparao

Commands:

docker volume create abcbank

docker volume ls

docker volume inspect abcbank

Description:

A Docker volume named abcbank was created for persistent storage. The volume details and storage location were verified.

Output:

Volume Name : abcbank

Storage Location:

/var/lib/docker/volumes/abcbank/_data

Volume created successfully.

---

TASK-6 : VOLUME MAPPING

Assigned User : Mani

Commands:

docker run -itd --name vks2 -v abcbank:/project1 -p 8081:80 suresh bash

docker exec -it vks2 bash

docker inspect vks2

Description:

The Docker volume abcbank was attached to container vks2 through the mount path /project1. This enabled persistent data storage inside the container.

Output:

Container Name : vks2

Volume Mapping Successful

---

TASK-7 : DATA PERSISTENCE VERIFICATION 

Assigned User : Srinu

Commands:

docker exec -it vks2 bash

cd /project1

nano customer.html

Content:

ABC Bank Customer Portal

cat customer.html

docker rm -f vks2

docker run -it d --name vks3 -v abcbank:/project1 -p 8082:80 suresh bash 

docker exec -it vks3 bash  

cat /project1/customer.html   

Description: 

A file named customer.html was created inside the mounted directory. After deleting container vks2, a new container named vks3 was created using the same Docker volume. The stored file was successfully retrieved, confirming persistent storage.

Output:

ABC Bank Customer Portal

Persistent Storage Verified Successfully

